Package: fastsemR
Title: R Interface to the fastsem SEM Estimator
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Luis", "Araujo", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "lf.araujo@pm.me",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7987-8765"))
Description: Provides R bindings to the fastsem structural equation modelling
    engine, a compiled Nim library that supports ML, DWLS, and FIML estimators
    with optional GPU acceleration. The package translates umx/OpenMx RAM
    model objects into fastsem lavaan syntax, fits the model, and injects
    the estimates back so that standard OpenMx summary and comparison tools
    continue to work. Multi-group models, definition variables, equality
    constraints, parameter bounds, and cluster-robust standard errors are
    all supported. The compiled binary is downloaded automatically from
    GitHub Releases on first use.
